1. PARCM STREAMLIT APP – “PARCM Processor”

Launching the PARCM App
	1.	Open VS Code.
	2.	Open the folder where the repo is cloned.
	3.	Open the VS Code terminal.
	4.	Navigate to the PARCM app folder (cd into the correct path).
	5.	Run: streamlit run grid_app.py
	6.	The browser will open the “PARCM Processor” app.

Running the PARCM Process
	1.	On the landing screen, select the Domain (Application).
	2.	Select the Reporting Month (choose any date in the month you’re reporting).
	3.	Click “Generate Exclusion Dataset.”
	4.	A progress bar will appear. The app will execute SQL code stored in Bitbucket to pull:
	•	PARCM metrics
	•	All failure-level data for the selected domain
	5.	Once completed, the PARCM metrics table is populated and all detail tabs are loaded.

Working with PARCM Metrics
	1.	The first tab shows raw PARCM metrics: Pass Count, Fail Count, Total Count, Percent Pass, Status.
	2.	These values are pre-RCA.
	3.	After RCA is complete, return to this tab and update:
	•	Pass Count
	•	Fail Count
	•	Total Count
	•	Percent Passed
	•	Status

Reviewing Failure Details
	1.	Each control type has its own tab (Downstream SLAs, Extract DQ Failures, Extract Non-DQ Failures, GVR REST API, Upstream SLAs).
	2.	Click the tabs to review all failures for that control type.
	3.	Use these tables for RCA and exclusions.

Exporting to Excel
	1.	After the exclusion dataset is generated, click “Generate and Download Summary.”
	2.	This exports the full PARCM dataset into Excel.
	3.	Use the Excel file for offline RCA work if needed.

Generating ORCIT Upload Template
	1.	Scroll to the bottom.
	2.	Click “Generate ORCIT.”
	3.	The app will generate an Excel file in the correct ORCIT bulk-upload format.
	4.	Use this for monthly ORCIT upload.

Generating the PARCM PowerPoint
	1.	Once metrics are finalized, click “Generate PPTX.”
	2.	The app creates the PARCM PowerPoint and populates the metrics into the deck.

Submitting Final Data to the Database
	1.	After all RCA and metric updates are completed, click “Submit to DB.”
	2.	The app writes your results to the Controls schema (CONTROLS_TECHADS_METRICS tables).

⸻

2. DAILY DQ STREAMLIT APP – “Daily DQ Checks”

Launching the Daily DQ App
	1.	Open VS Code.
	2.	Navigate to the Daily DQ folder in the repo.
	3.	Run: streamlit run grid_app.py
	4.	The browser will open the “Daily DQ Checks” app.

Running the Daily DQ Report
	1.	On the landing screen, select a Check Type (SLA, GVR, Intra Day, API, Nulls, Dupes, Deviation).
	•	This selection only determines which tab you start on.
	2.	Click “Run Report.”
	3.	The app executes all Daily DQ SQL queries:
	•	SLA
	•	GVR
	•	Intra Day
	•	API
	•	Nulls
	•	Dupes
	•	Deviation
	4.	The app loads the failure results for each check type and caches them.
	5.	A success message appears (e.g., “Grid refreshed successfully”).

Reviewing Failures by Control Type
	1.	After the run, use the tabs at the bottom to view failures for each control:
	•	SLA
	•	GVR
	•	Intra Day
	•	API
	•	Nulls
	•	Dupes
	•	Deviation
	2.	Each tab contains the detailed failure list for that control.
	3.	Analysts review these for the daily RCA process.

Downloading the Daily DQ Excel
	1.	Click “Download Excel” after the run completes.
	2.	The file includes all failures for that reporting day, organized by control type.
	3.	Add RCA notes or adjust statuses as needed.

Sending the Daily DQ Email
	1.	When RCA and Excel updates are complete, return to the app.
	2.	Click “Send Email.”
	3.	The app sends the Daily DQ email using the configured distribution list.
	4.	This completes the Daily DQ workflow for the day.

⸻

Relationship Between the Two Apps

Daily DQ App:
	•	Handles daily failures for all DQ control types.
	•	Used for daily BAU checks, Excel generation, and email notifications.

PARCM App:
	•	Handles monthly PARCM metrics for selected domains.
	•	Used to calculate Key Measure metrics, review failures, generate PPT, create ORCIT files, and submit results to the DB.